rComments: He's so cute :) and hes a really great english prof! He engages with the class and is very kind to his students, and he responds well to class participation. I felt like i had a new appreciation for poetry after his class!

His lectures were hard to follow, as he is often reading long paragraphs directly off of his powerpoint slides. He relies too much on class participation to fill time and to convey information, and so he comes across as unprepared. Getting clear instructions for assignments was difficult, even after email exchanges.

He's great! Interesting lectures, very engaging, even if you're shy, don't hesitate to raise your hand, the structure of his classes thrive off of student participation. Most of the poems in the textbook can be found online and the plays are dirt cheap. Tough marker like most other English profs but the assignments aren't very long.

Really interesting class. Reading the poemsplays before the class will help. Essays assigned aren't very long, 2-3 pages for the first two and approx. 6 for the research essay. Marking was fair with good feedback and questions over email are answered quickly and are helpful.
